interlinear-text.item: Blaser, Magdalena "Myths of the Cofán people"

word.item: Many years ago, a man named Shaningipi lived at the Aguarico river bank with his family.
She lived for many years with her parents,
and grew old withough even thinking of getting married.
But one might she had a dream of a handsome young man.
First, she didn't think much of that dream at all.
But once dreamt, the dream would come back,
unfalteringly, every single night. So she started to think:
"Perhaps I really want to get married."
and in doing so, she truly fell in love with the man of her dreams.
so they made love at night.
